CHAIN OF RESPONSIBILITY(COR):
Lets say we have a Client who sends a requests to object. It usually doesnt send 
request to one single object.There might be multiple objects.(Chain of objects)

Ex:
Client---> | R1, R2, R3 | R1, R2, R3 are 3 different objects and R1 has R2;s ref simlarly R2 has R3's. (Links like in Linked List)
Now R1 checks whether it can fulfil the client requests. If yes it does or else sends it to R2 and again R2 checks 
 whether it can be done by it or further send it to R3.

 So there are objects connected by chain and if they client sends it s request to first object

Ex: ATM
In ATM every denomination is handled seperately by multiple handlers. 
H1--1000 (x5), H2--500 (x10), H3--100(x20)
And client request is 6000
So H1 checks whether it can fulfil it of not requests goes to H2
 In this condition 5000 is handled by H1 and remaining is sent to H2 for remaining 1000

 What is difference between LL and COR:
 LL:Stores the data and next pointer points to same object i.r can be reffered further only when they are same.
 COR: It handles req but doesnot store data. and next pointer can point even if they arent same/similar objects.

 But in over simplified view they are same. Multiple objects are connected.

 